      • getInstance

        public <T> T getInstance(java.lang.Class<T> type,
                         java.lang.Class<?> module,
                         InjectorProperty<?>... additionalProperties)
        Gets an instance of a provided Class type. If the type is annotated with Module it is ran through the ModuleManager instance to obtain the instance. If it is not annotated as such, it is ran through the instance Injector to obtain the instance based on implementation, or manually, provided mappings.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type parameter for the instance to return
        Parameters:
        type - The type of the instance
        module - The type of the module if module specific bindings are to be used
        additionalProperties - The properties to be passed into the type either during or after construction
        Returns:
        The instance, if present. Otherwise returns null

      • bindUtility

        public <T> void bindUtility(java.lang.Class<T> contract,
                            java.lang.Class<? extends T> implementation)
        Creates a custom binding for a given contract and implementation using a custom AbstractModule. Requires the implementation to extend the contract type.

        The binding is created by Guice, and can be annotated using Guice supported annotations (e.g. Singleton)

        Type Parameters:
        T - The type parameter of the contract
        Parameters:
        contract - The class type of the contract
        implementation - The class type of the implementation
